+## Anthropic Claude with a Pro/Max plan
+
+Use Anthropic Claude models through a Claude Pro/Max subscription without API
+keys or `config.toml` edits.
+
+Sign in once:
+
+```bash
+grok anthropic login
+```
+
+The browser flow uses Anthropic's PKCE authorization flow and a fixed callback
+at `http://localhost:53692/callback`. When the browser runs on another
+machine, paste the redirect URL or the `code#state` pair shown by claude.ai
+into the terminal. Credentials are stored separately from the xAI session in
+`~/.grok/anthropic_auth.json`, refreshed automatically, and sent only to the
+Anthropic API.
+
+After login, the `anthropic/*` models appear in the Ctrl+M picker. Switch
+inside the app with a pi-style provider/model reference and optional thinking
+level:
+
+```
+/model anthropic/claude-opus-4-8:high
+/model anthropic/claude-sonnet-5:max
+```
+
+The equivalent CLI form is:
+
+```bash
+grok -m anthropic/claude-opus-4-8:high -p "hello"
+```
+
+Claude models offer thinking levels `low` through `max`. Native `xhigh` — a
+distinct level between `high` and `max` — is available on Opus 4.7/4.8,
+Sonnet 5, and Fable 5; on Opus 4.6 and Sonnet 4.6, a requested `xhigh`
+resolves to `max`.
+
+Use `grok anthropic status` to inspect the credential and
+`grok anthropic logout` to remove it. Anthropic login does not replace or
+modify the normal `grok login` session.
+
