-The `messages` backend uses the Anthropic Messages protocol. Anthropic authenticates with an `x-api-key` header rather than `Authorization: Bearer`, so pass your key through `extra_headers`, which Grok sends verbatim.
+The `messages` backend uses the Anthropic Messages protocol. With an API key, Anthropic authenticates with an `x-api-key` header rather than `Authorization: Bearer`, so pass your key through `extra_headers`, which Grok sends verbatim.
+
+For Claude Pro/Max OAuth, do **not** configure a key manually; use the
+built-in `anthropic/*` catalog described above. Advanced custom entries can
+opt into the stored Anthropic credential with
+`auth_scheme = "anthropic_oauth"`, `api_backend = "messages"`, and
+`base_url = "https://api.anthropic.com/v1"`; Grok then injects the Claude
+Code identity headers and system block that the consumer-OAuth backend
+requires. In custom entries, only offer the `xhigh` effort on models with
+native `xhigh` support (Opus 4.7/4.8, Sonnet 5, Fable 5); it passes through
+verbatim on the Messages wire, and older models reject it — use `max`
+instead, which every adaptive Claude model accepts.
 
